#. type: Plain text
#: origin/remotex.txt:6
msgid "SYNOPSIS: This hint explains how to setup and and get working remote X."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/remotex.txt:8
msgid "HINT:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/remotex.txt:14
msgid ""
"Setting up remote X is very simple.  You need two computers... one will be "
"called A and one will be called B.  An X server needs to be running on A.  "
"To allow computer B to connect to computer A's X server, you need to run "
"'xhost +Bip' on computer A.  Than you have to follow the directions based on "
"how you are connecting to computer B."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/remotex.txt:19
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are using ssh and have 'ForwardX11 yes' in your config:\n"
"\tYou don't have to setup anything special, all you have to do is ssh\n"
"\tinto computer B from computer A and run the programs normally, the ssh\n"
"\twill do everything for you.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/remotex.txt:24
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are using telnet or you can't put 'ForwardX11 yes' in your config:\n"
"\tMake sure port 6000 is open on computer A.  Telnet or ssh into computer\n"
"\tB and type 'export DISPLAY=Aip:0'.  Then you can just run programs like\n"
"\tyou normally would.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/remotex.txt:26
msgid "If it works, you should see the program you ran display on computer A."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/remotex.txt:27
msgid "Enjoy!"
msgstr ""
